<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 lies between the regions of Aosta Valley, Italy, and Haute-Savoie, France. The location of the summit itself is a subject of controversy between the two countries, as each tends to place it within its own boundaries on maps. In a convention between France and Kingdom of Sardinia, in Turin (1861), the border was fixed on the highest point of 
<REF ID="767.5" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Monte Bianco</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Monte Bianco itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
. This was the last official definition of this border, but often the French maps do not respect this solution.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
The two most famous towns near 
<REF ID="767.6" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mont Blanc itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Monte Bianco</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Monte Bianco itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 are Courmayeur, in Aosta Valley, Italy, and Chamonix, in Haute-Savoie, France - the site of the first Winter Olympics.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Begun in 1957 and completed in 1965, the 11.6 km (7Â¼ mi) Mont Blanc Tunnel runs beneath 
<REF ID="767.7" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
